{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.31",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 31 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:1",
      "text": "“I have made a covenant with my eyes; how then could I look upon a virgin?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:2",
      "text": "What would be my portion from God above, and my heritage from the Almighty on high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:3",
      "text": "Does not calamity befall the unrighteous, and disaster the workers of iniquity?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:4",
      "text": "Does not he see my ways, and number all my steps?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:5",
      "text": "“If I have walked with falsehood, and my foot has hastened to deceit;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:6",
      "text": "(Let me be weighed in a just balance, and let God know my integrity!)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:7",
      "text": "if my step has turned aside from the way, and my heart has gone after my eyes, and if any spot has cleaved to my hands;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:8",
      "text": "then let me sow, and another eat; and let what grows for me be rooted out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:9",
      "text": "“If my heart has been enticed to a woman, and I have lain in wait at my neighbor's door;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:10",
      "text": "then let my wife grind for another, and let others bow down upon her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:11",
      "text": "For that would be a heinous crime; that would be an iniquity to be punished by the judges;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:12",
      "text": "for that would be a fire which consumes unto Abaddon, and it would burn to the root all my increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:13",
      "text": "“If I have rejected the cause of my manservant or my maidservant, when they brought a complaint against me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:14",
      "text": "what then shall I do when God rises up? When he makes inquiry, what shall I answer him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:15",
      "text": "Did not he who made me in the womb make him? And did not one fashion us in the womb?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:16",
      "text": "“If I have withheld anything that the poor desired, or have caused the eyes of the widow to fail,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:17",
      "text": "or have eaten my morsel alone, and the fatherless has not eaten of it",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:18",
      "text": "(for from his youth I reared him as a father, and from his mother's womb I guided him);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:19",
      "text": "if I have seen any one perish for lack of clothing, or a poor man without covering;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:20",
      "text": "if his loins have not blessed me, and if he was not warmed with the fleece of my sheep;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:21",
      "text": "if I have raised my hand against the fatherless, because I saw help in the gate;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:22",
      "text": "then let my shoulder blade fall from my shoulder, and let my arm be broken from its socket.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:23",
      "text": "For I was in terror of calamity from God, and I could not have faced his majesty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:24",
      "text": "“If I have made gold my trust, or called fine gold my confidence;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:25",
      "text": "if I have rejoiced because my wealth was great, or because my hand had gotten much;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:26",
      "text": "if I have looked at the sun when it shone, or the moon moving in splendor,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:27",
      "text": "and my heart has been secretly enticed, and my mouth has kissed my hand;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:28",
      "text": "this also would be an iniquity to be punished by the judges, for I should have been false to God above.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:29",
      "text": "“If I have rejoiced at the ruin of him that hated me, or exulted when evil overtook him",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:30",
      "text": "(I have not let my mouth sin by asking for his life with a curse);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:31",
      "text": "if the men of my tent have not said, ‘Who is there that has not been filled with his meat?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:32",
      "text": "(the sojourner has not lodged in the street; I have opened my doors to the wayfarer);",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:33",
      "text": "if I have concealed my transgressions from men, by hiding my iniquity in my bosom,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:34",
      "text": "because I stood in great fear of the multitude, and the contempt of families terrified me, so that I kept silence, and did not go out of doors—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:35",
      "text": "Oh, that I had one to hear me! (Here is my signature! let the Almighty answer me!) Oh, that I had the indictment written by my adversary!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:36",
      "text": "Surely I would carry it on my shoulder; I would bind it on me as a crown;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:37",
      "text": "I would give him an account of all my steps; like a prince I would approach him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:38",
      "text": "“If my land has cried out against me, and its furrows have wept together;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:39",
      "text": "if I have eaten its yield without payment, and caused the death of its owners;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.31.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:40",
      "text": "let thorns grow instead of wheat, and foul weeds instead of barley.” The words of Job are ended.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
